    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It would be really useful to have a way to catch/handle signals in Cython. In fact the `try...except` syntax explored in [this wiki page]( https://github.com/cython/cython/wiki/enhancements-signals ) would be great.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "There's [cysignals](https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/3192) for that purpose.\r\n\r\nI'm not sure if it's really better to make signals a language feature, nor if `try-except-finally` is a good way to handle signals. They can often be (pre-)processed out of order and may or may not have an impact on the control flow. `try-except-finally` always changes the control flow.",
